After  jenkins create jar then check in ubuntu like this 
So:
Open Ubuntu normally.
Run:
ls /mnt/c/ProgramData/Jenkins/.jenkins/workspace/p8/target
If everything is accessible, you should see something like:
simple-maven-project-with-tests-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar


Step 1: Create deployment folder
Run:
mkdir -p ~/deployment

Step 2: Create hosts.ini
Run:
nano hosts.ini
Paste:
[servers]
localhost ansible_connection=local
Save:
Ctrl+O
Enter
Ctrl+X

Step 3: Create deploy.yml
Run:
nano deploy.yml
Paste exactly:
---
- name: Deploy Maven Artifact
 hosts: servers
 connection: local

 tasks:

   - name: Create deployment directory
     file:
       path: /home/sanikagl/deployment
       state: directory

   - name: Copy JAR file
     copy:
       src: /mnt/c/ProgramData/Jenkins/.jenkins/workspace/p8/target/simple-maven-project-with-tests-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar
       dest: /home/sanikagl/deployment/
Save:
Ctrl+O
Enter
Ctrl+X

Step 4: Run the playbook
Execute:
ansible-playbook -i hosts.ini deploy.yml

Step 5: Verify deployment
Run:
ls ~/deployment
You should see:
simple-maven-project-with-tests-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

